{#
   agent/symptom_description.j2

   Pure symptom description prompt — Node 5.

   Critically: this prompt NEVER mentions disease names.
   The model describes only what it physically observes.
   This feeds RAG retrieval and differential diagnosis but
   does not anchor on any disease label prematurely.

   Variables:
   - crop:         identified crop name e.g. "cotton"
   - weather_data: optional dict with temperature, humidity, disease_risk
#}
You are examining a {{ crop }} leaf.

{% if weather_data %}
Current weather context:
- Temperature: {{ weather_data.temperature }}°C
- Humidity: {{ weather_data.humidity }}%
- Disease risk level: {{ weather_data.disease_risk | default("unknown") }}
{% if weather_data.humidity > 80 %}
Note: High humidity increases fungal disease risk on this crop.
{% endif %}
{% if weather_data.temperature > 35 %}
Note: Temperatures above 35°C can cause heat stress symptoms.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

Describe ONLY what you physically observe on this leaf.
Do NOT name any disease, pathogen, pest, or condition.
Do NOT make any diagnosis.

For every observation, describe:
1. Location — where on the leaf (edge, centre, veins, tip, whole leaf)
2. Colour — exact colours and any changes from normal
3. Texture — powdery, water-soaked, dry, sunken, raised, greasy
4. Pattern — uniform, angular, circular, interveinal, ring-shaped, random
5. Any growth — mold, pustules, ooze, webbing, sticky residue
6. Distribution — scattered, clustered, marginal, tip-only, whole plant

Be specific and objective. Describe what you see, not what you think it is.

Note: If the leaf appears completely healthy with no abnormalities,
describe the normal morphological features — colour, texture, vein
pattern, size — so the crop can still be identified and a healthy
result returned. Do not force disease symptoms where none exist.
